According to the 2010 census,<ref name="GR8">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=September 19, 2016|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> 1772 people were living in La Mesilla. The population density was 151.9 inhabitants per square kilometer. Of the 1772 inhabitants, La Mesilla was composed by 68.34% White, 0.34% were [[African American]], 1.35% were Native American, 0.4% were Asian, 0% were [[Pacific Islanders]], the 25.62% were of other races and 3.95% from two or more races. Of the total population 73.36% were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race<ref>[https://geonames.usgs.gov/ U.S. Board on Geographic Names]</ref>

